  ],
  "remarks": "Alexander Sanchik is a Russian military leader, former Commander of the Eastern Military District (from May 2024 until November 2024) and is currently the acting Commander of the South Group of Forces (since November 2024), former First Deputy Commander of the Eastern Military District (from 2023 to 2024) and former Commander of the 35th Combined Arms Army. The 35th Combined Arms Army attacked Ukraine from the north. As Commander of the 35th Combined Arms Army, he was responsible for the actions of his unit. Alexander Sanchik is therefore responsible for supporting and implementing actions which undermine the territorial integrity, sovereignty and independence of Ukraine.",
